description.narrative: Despite the COVID-19 context, most activities planned were implemented and key targets reached. UNICEF supported the integration of 27,338 out-of-school children through catch-up and alternative education strategies, including innovative interventions such as activities targeting children accommodated in traditional Quranic schools (‘daaras’), the introduction of distance learning modalities for school dropouts, and the deployment of alternative training opportunities for vulnerable youths on marketable and entrepreneurial skills. Strategies promoting girls’ education including on menstrual hygiene management were scaled up benefiting additional regions, and the learning environment of 8,226 schools was improved, including on COVID19-related school reopening protocols, benefiting overall 1,598,552 learners. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:03/02/2022
